<br>\
Your analysis can start from these perspectives:&nbsp;<br>\
<br>\
</span></div><ol><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Media and Medium: Describe the type of media and the medium used in the artwork. Consider how these elements influence the viewer's perception and the piece's impact.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Style and Historical Context: Examine the artistic style and historical context of the artwork. Discuss how these aspects contribute to its meaning and significance within the art world and media studies.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Artist Information: Provide relevant information about the artist, including their background, influences, and other notable works. Explore how the artist\'92s perspective and experiences shape the artwork.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Theoretical Analysis: Apply media theories we discussed in the class to your analysis, exploring how the artwork communicates ideas, emotions, or critiques societal issues.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Speculation and Future Directions: Speculate on how the artwork could inspire new directions or discussions in media practice.&nbsp;</span><hr></div></li></ol><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Format:<br></span></div><ol><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Prepare a 7 minutes presentation that addresses at least three points above</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Include visuals of the artwork and relevant supporting materials.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Be ready to engage the class in a discussion about your analysis and insights into how the artwork can inform and inspire media studies.</span></div><hr></li></ol><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);"><ul class="lineated"><li>Time Limit: 7 Minutes + 1 QA<br></li><li>Due: Presentation Day, <span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Upload your Creative Reflection Presentation deck to Canvas.</span><br></span></li></ul></span></div><br></column-unit></column-set><hr><column-set><column-unit slot="0" span="2"><br>\
