 Speculative Media <br>25 Points</span></div></column-unit><column-unit slot="1" span="10"><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Description:</span></div><ol><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Students will work in groups of 4-6 to conduct a speculative media analysis. Each group will focus on a specific media topic, such as cinema, gaming, television, or XR media. Within their chosen topic, groups can either:</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Precedure: Students should form groups during the <u>first week of November</u>, with each student taking responsibility for a distinct section. </span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Conduct an in-depth analysis of a single technological artifact, exploring its potential evolution over the next 1 to 10 years.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Conduct an overall analysis of the medium, examining different aspects and speculating on its future(1-10 years) developments and impact.</span></div></li><ol></ol></ol><br>\
<div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Assignment Details:<span style="font-size: calc(var(--font-scale) * var(--font-size)); letter-spacing: 0em;"></span><span style="font-size: calc(var(--font-scale) * var(--font-size)); letter-spacing: 0em;"><br><ol><li>\
Group Composition: Each group should consist of 4-6 students. Collaborate to choose a media topic and decide on either a focused or broad analysis approach</li><li>Artifact or Medium Focus:<br>A. For an in-depth analysis, select a specific technological artifact (e.g., traditional filmmaking, VR gaming systems) and speculate on its future developments.<br>\
B. For an overall analysis, explore the broader media landscape (e.g., cinema's multiplatform availability) and speculate on its evolution and impact.<br></li><li>Analysis Framework:<br>\
A.Technical Aspect (Form): Examine the design, affordances, and interactions of the technology.<br>\
B. Organizational (Creators): Identify the creators, their values, and how these influence the technology.<br>\
C. Cultural: Analyze the cultural context, embedded values, and intended users, considering who might be excluded.<br>\
D. Speculation: Project the future of the technology or medium, considering positive, negative, and neutral aspects, and how form, organization, and culture may evolve.<br>\
E. Use of Authors: Incorporate insights from at least three authors studied in class, plus one additional author your group researches. Use these sources to support your analysis and speculation.</li></ol></span></span><hr><span style="font-size: calc(var(--font-scale) * var(--font-size)); letter-spacing: 0em; color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Format:</span></div><ol><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Each group submit a written essay: 6000- 9000 words, submitted as a PDF to Canvas.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Use a standard academic format, with an abstract, introduction, body, and conclusion. Include a cohesive thesis statement and support your claims with evidence.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Cite all sources, including class readings and any additional media, using MLA citation style.</span></div></li><li><div style="text-align: left"><span style="color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Proofread and refine your work before submission to ensure clarity and coherence.</span><hr></div></li></ol><div style="text-align: left"><div style="text-align: center"><span style="font-size: calc(var(--font-scale) * var(--font-size)); letter-spacing: 0em; color: rgb(68, 55, 21);">Due: 10th, December, 08:00.P.M.</span></div></div></column-unit></column-set><br>\
<br>\
</div><br>\
